---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Robin van Baalen" description="Almost thirty years building software. AI, bleeding edge tools, and an obsession with the details that shape how software feels.">
  <section class="relative mb-16">
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -inset-x-6 -inset-y-20 z-[-1] sm:-inset-x-40" style={`background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 8% 15%, oklch(62% 0.04 260 / var(--gradient-intensity)), transparent 50%);`} aria-hidden="true" />
    <h1 class="mb-6 text-[36px] font-normal leading-[1.1] tracking-tight text-primary sm:text-[60px]" data-kinetic-hero>
      I build because I love it.
    </h1>
  </section>

  <script>
    function initKineticHero() {
      const hero = document.querySelector("[data-kinetic-hero]");
      if (!hero || window.matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)").matches) return;
      if (hero.hasAttribute("data-kinetic-done")) return;
      hero.setAttribute("data-kinetic-done", "");

      const text = hero.textContent || "";
      const words = text.trim().split(/\s+/);
      while (hero.firstChild) hero.removeChild(hero.firstChild);

      words.forEach((word, i) => {
        const span = document.createElement("span");
        span.style.display = "inline-block";
        span.style.opacity = "0";
        span.style.transform = "translateY(10px)";
        span.style.animation = `word-in 500ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) ${150 + i * 100}ms forwards`;
        span.textContent = word + "\u00A0";
        hero.appendChild(span);
      });
    }
    initKineticHero();
    document.addEventListener("astro:page-load", initKineticHero);
  </script>

  <div class="max-w-xl space-y-6">
    <p class="text-lg text-primary leading-relaxed">
      I've been building software for almost thirty years — it's my work, my passion, and my hobby. The tools keep getting better, and right now they're moving faster than ever.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-primary leading-relaxed">
      AI redefined what a single builder can ship. I use it every day, stay on the bleeding edge, and build things that weren't possible a year ago. But what hasn't changed is what I care about: the details. The tiniest transition, the spacing between elements, the right color scheme — that's not polish, that's the product.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
